FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31009
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774962671
OL,3,CWhat to know as countdown begins for
OL,4,Cfirst human Moon mission in 53 years
OL,6,FToday, it is China who are rapidly
OL,7,Fadvancing their space programme,
OL,8,Fhaving achieved a series of successful
OL,9,Frobotic and rover landings on the
OL,10,FMoon. It has announced plans to send
OL,11,Fastronauts there by 2030.
OL,13,FThe Moon is home to a wealth of
OL,14,Fvaluable minerals, and the two
OL,15,Fcountries are effectively in a race to
OL,16,Faccess to the areas of the it with the
OL,17,Fbest resources.
OL,19,FWho is the crew and how dangerous is
OL,20,Fthe mission for them?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31010
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774962671
OL,3,CWhat to know as countdown begins for
OL,4,Cfirst human Moon mission in 53 years
OL,6,FFour astronauts will make up the crew
OL,7,Ffor Artemis II.
OL,9,FThree of the crew, Reid Wiseman
OL,10,F(commander), Victor Glover (pilot) and
OL,11,FChristina Koch (mission specialist)
OL,12,Fare Americans who have all been to
OL,13,Fspace previously.
OL,15,FThe fourth crew member, Mission
OL,16,FSpecialist Jeremy Hansen, has not been
OL,17,Fto space and will make history as the
OL,18,Ffirst Canadian to fly around the moon.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31011
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774962671
OL,3,CWhat to know as countdown begins for
OL,4,Cfirst human Moon mission in 53 years
OL,6,FArtemis II is by no means a risk free
OL,7,Fmission, as the crew will be in a
OL,8,Fspacecraft that has never been used by
OL,9,Fhumans before.
OL,11,FMany tests will be undertaken while
OL,12,Fthey are in the Earth orbit, so there
OL,13,Fis less far to travel should they
OL,14,Fexperience issues.
OL,16,FThe Orion spacecraft crew capsule is
OL,17,Fonly about 5m wide by 3m high, and all
OL,18,Ffour crew members will work, eat and
OL,19,Fsleep there.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31012
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774962671
OL,3,CWhat to know as countdown begins for
OL,4,Cfirst human Moon mission in 53 years
OL,6,FWhen is launch day and could it be
OL,7,Fdelayed?
OL,9,FAfter being postponed once due to bad
OL,10,Fweather in February, and then again
OL,11,Fafter the liquid hydrogen leak, there
OL,12,Fare always potential issues when
OL,13,Fplanning a high-stake mission.
OL,15,FThe weather is an important factor in
OL,16,Fwhether the mission will be able to go
OL,17,Fahead.
OL,19,FLightning is a big safety risk, due to
OL,20,Fthe Artemis II rocket containing vast
OL,21,Famounts of propellant.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
